\section{Conclusion}
\lipsum[10-12]

\end{document}
```
This example document contains the following sections:

1. Introduction
2. First Section
3. Second Section
4. Conclusion

The `tocbasic` package is used to generate the table of contents, and the `\tableofcontents` command is placed after the title but before the body of the document. The `tocbasic` package does not provide a formatted ToC like the standard `toc` package, but it can be used in situations where the standard ToC commands are not available, such as in `\include`d documents.

If you want a more formatted ToC, you can use the standard `toc` package. Here's an example:
```latex
